             sworn.</p>
               <p>I saw the prisoner come out of the house with something in his hand; he walked<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="178801090004"></xptr>on, I did not see him stopped; Mr. Pearcey came out of the door, I told him there was the man, and Mr. Pearcey stopped the man; he was never out of my sight till he was stopped.</p>
               <p>(The ham produced and deposed to.)</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I never was in the house, I was on the other side of the way.</p>
               <p>Jury. What time in the evening was it? - A quarter before six.</p>
               <p>Court. Was this man known here before? - No.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17880109-2-verdict9" type="verdictDescription">
